{
    "description_long": "This object is a detailed grave site ensemble, featuring a large stone tomb with a sloped top and two rectangular metal plaques embedded on its surface. At the head of the tomb, there is a prominent upright headstone with a carved cross, flanked by a smaller rectangular stone marker at its base. The materials appear to be primarily gray granite or marble, with metallic insets for inscriptions or decoration. The structure is solid and heavy, with clean, angular lines and a weathered, matte finish typical of outdoor cemetery monuments. The overall design suggests a traditional Western-style grave, suitable for placement in a formal cemetery or memorial park.",
